{
  "text": "Individual SOCS proteins are able to inhibit a variety of different cytokines [CITATION_1] and in general the induction of SOCS upon cytokine stimulation is indicative that the respective cytokine is regulated in a feedback mode. In a slightly different system it has also been observed that SOCS-1 and SOCS-3 are induced in immature DCs by addition of IL-4 and GM-CSF, respectively [CITATION_2] . GM-CSF signaling, on the other hand, is subject to inhibition by SOCS-1.",
